<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="332" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d332">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/545.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <hi rend="italic"><date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1912-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1912-01-16T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>;
                                    received January 17, 1912</hi>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Those of the opposition who want trouble are saying that the second
                            paragraph of the note I handed to the President yesterday means a demand
                            by the United States for a complete return to the status quo ante by
                            immediate repeal of the new civil service law amendments. The President
                            answers that it means merely that he shall not revoke the decree
                            forbidding officers attending Veteran meetings, and court martial for
                            the disobedient, with no further unlawful concessions to the Veterans.
                            He earnestly requests that Department let him know if he is correct.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>